The paper also discusses the use of belief propagation decoding on memoryless channels, which falls under the category of network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also touches upon the topic of coded modulation, which is related to signal processing and communication (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of iterative bounds, which is related to the field of dynamical systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of soft bit values for a maximum a posteriori probability (MAP) decoder, which is related to machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.MM).
